oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Chestnut Mound
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The hills near Chestnut Mound, Tennessee, on U.S. Highway 70. The area seems to have been cleared for agricultural purposes. A wire fence with wooden posts divides the areas. In the background are mountains.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
